        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Current environmental campaigns rely on moral obligation or low-value point systems, which often fail to engage Gen Z. GreenBattle innovates by leveraging a dopamine-driven competitive game loop. We shift the narrative from an obligatory chore to an exciting survival mechanic-players don't just pick up trash; they hunt for resources to win. Furthermore, our two-step validation process (Scanning Trash -> Scanning Bin) naturally acts as an anti-cheat mechanism, forcing physical movement and ensuring the waste is properly disposed of.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "Our system is designed for high performance and low latency on mobile devices:\n\nFrontend & Camera: Built with React Native utilizing react-native-vision-camera to handle real-time frame processing and deliver a seamless native AR experience.\n\nEdge AI: We deploy lightweight Computer Vision models (like YOLOv8 or MobileNet) directly on the device using react-native-fast-tflite. This allows instant, offline object detection for both the waste items and the designated trash bins without relying on cloud processing.\n\nBackend & Real-time Multiplayer: We use a serverless architecture with Supabase. WebSockets handle the real-time synchronization of player coordinates, inventory states, and AR combat interactions.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Public Services",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Environmental Impact: Large-scale, community-driven cleanup of public spaces, significantly reducing the amount of misplaced plastic waste.\n\nBehavioral Shift: Rewiring micro-habits. By gamifying the process, we aim to build a conditioned reflex where users automatically identify and properly sort waste, eventually doing so even when the application is closed.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "IoT Smart Bin Integration: Evolving the app to interact directly with sensor-equipped smart recycling bins. Instead of a camera scan, depositing real waste into the bin automatically triggers a signal to the app to reload ammunition.\n\nB2B Gamified Marketing: Partnering with FMCG brands (e.g., beverage companies) to sponsor in-game rewards. Scanning a sponsor's branded bottle or depositing waste at their specific event stations could unlock exclusive, branded in-game weapons or character skins.",
