        "Name of your project": "BridgeVoice",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "BridgeVoice is a compact, portable device (earpiece or pocket unit) for two-way, real-time Vietnamese ↔ English/Chinese/Korean translation. All AI runs fully on-device on a Snapdragon NPU - no internet, no cloud. Low-latency streaming (~1.5s), built for noisy FDI factory floors where cloud tools fail.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Fully on-device & offline - runs entirely on a Snapdragon NPU, while most translation tools depend on cloud/internet that factory floors lack.\nClause-level streaming - starts translating mid-utterance using a wait-k policy, instead of waiting for a full sentence or naively translating word-by-word (which breaks grammar, especially for SOV languages like Korean).\nCode-switching aware - handles real factory speech where Vietnamese is mixed with English/technical terms, not just clean single-language input.\nOn-device domain vocabulary - factory-specific terminology (machine names, safety terms, abbreviations) loaded as hotwords + swappable LoRA adapters, with no network needed.\nNoise-robust - far-field recognition tuned for high-noise industrial environments.\nMeasured on real silicon - quality optimized as latency ÷ (memory × power) on actual Qualcomm hardware via AI Hub, not just accuracy on paper.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "Hardware: Snapdragon device (Hexagon NPU) + mic/speaker. Demo on reference device; pocket wearable is target form.\nPipeline: mic → noise reduction + VAD → speech recognition → translation → speech synthesis → speaker. Fully offline, clause-level streaming.\nSpeech recognition (ASR): FunASR (Fun-ASR-Nano) - unified Vi/En/Zh/Ko, code-switching aware, far-field noise-robust, built-in VAD + diarization + hotword. Edge GGUF (~484 MB).\nMachine translation (MT): commercial-friendly open MT model (license-vetted) + wait-k streaming + LoRA domain adapters. Final model to be selected after benchmarking.\nSpeech synthesis (TTS): VITS (streaming).\nOptimization: INT8/INT4 quantization; profile latency/memory/power on real silicon via Qualcomm AI Hub; VAD gating for battery.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–CN, VN–EN, VN–KR",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Workers: breaks the language barrier, safer, better-trained, more advancement. Businesses: fewer miscommunication errors/accidents, lower cost, higher productivity. Society: brings offline translation to connectivity-poor sites (factories, construction, remote areas).",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "Evolve from reference-device demo to a custom compact wearable (dual-mic, directional speaker, 8h+ battery). Use FedLoRA so factories improve domain terminology without sharing private data. Expand language pairs and industry vocab packs, integrate with factory safety/training systems, and pilot with FDI factories toward commercial rollout.",
