        "Name of your project": "OneVoice Smart Translator Badge",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "A 100% offline, chest-worn Edge AI translation device (Smart Badge) specifically designed for workers and professionals in noisy industrial environments. The solution enables natural bilingual communication (Vietnamese ↔ English, Mandarin, Korean) with ultra-low latency (< 1.5s). It is completely hands-free, does not block the user's hearing (ears-free for safety), and operates reliably in areas with no internet connectivity or strict data privacy requirements.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Unlike standard smartphone apps or tourist translation earbuds, our solution innovates in 4 core areas:\n\"Hands-Free & Ears-Free\" Industrial Design: A wearable badge with a single large tactile button and intuitive LED indicators allows workers to operate machinery with thick gloves while staying fully aware of ambient safety alarms.\nAI Safety Mode (Smart PPE): A background TinyML model continuously listens for emergency keywords (e.g., \"Fire\", \"Help\", \"Stop\") to instantly interrupt the translation pipeline, trigger heavy vibrations, and flash red SOS LEDs.\nFactory Vocabulary: Utilizes Contextual Biasing to accurately translate complex electromechanical and factory-specific terminology - an area where general-purpose translation AI frequently fails.\nStreaming Edge AI: Operates entirely independent of Cloud APIs, eliminating network-induced latency and completely preventing the risk of industrial data leaks.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "Our architecture features a hardware-agnostic Streaming AI pipeline, designed to transition seamlessly from a cost-effective proof-of-concept to enterprise-grade *Qualcomm hardware:Phased Hardware Strategy: To rapidly validate our \"Smart Badge\" form factor, ergonomics, and system logic (VAD, physical controls, LED indicators), our August prototype will utilize a low-cost Edge architecture (e.g., RK3566 or Hybrid MCU). For the Field Testing phase (October), we will migrate our pipeline to the competition's provided hardware, ensuring our solution is fully integrated with the Qualcomm ecosystem.\n*Qualcomm AI Hub Integration: Once the target hardware is acquired, we will leverage the Qualcomm AI Hub to deeply optimize our models (Whisper-tiny, Opus-MT, Piper). By converting our models to quantized INT8 formats specifically tuned for Snapdragon NPUs, we aim to push the End-to-End perceived latency well below 1.5 seconds.\n*Audio Frontend & TinyML Safety: The system implements Delay-and-Sum Beamforming with RNNoise to combat 85-100dB industrial noise. Concurrently, a lightweight TinyML model runs continuously to detect emergency keywords (\"Stop\", \"Fire\"), acting as a smart safety PPE feature.\n*Streaming AI Pipeline: We abandon traditional batch processing in favor of a continuous streaming pipeline (ASR -> NMT\n-> TTS), integrating Contextual Biasing to accurately translate complex factory vocabulary offline.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Prototype",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Our Smart Badge breaks language barriers in noisy factories and construction sites. It helps local workers and foreign managers communicate easily without using their hands. This reduces technical mistakes, saves time, and prevents accidents thanks to the emergency keyword detection. Ultimately, it creates a safer and more productive workplace for everyone.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "In the future, we plan to evolve the Smart Badge through three main steps. First, we will conduct pilot testing in real manufacturing factories and M&E construction sites to gather user feedback and improve our technical vocabulary models. Second, we will upgrade the hardware for mass production, focusing on making it water and dust resistant (IP rating) and extending battery life for 12-hour shifts. Finally, we aim to partner with industrial enterprises to deploy the badge as a standard piece of communication and safety equipment for their workforce.",
