        "Describe your technical approach": "We develop a high-performance Voice Orchestrator framework in C++, designed for portability across a wide range of platforms and operating systems. The architecture incorporates an abstraction layer for inference engines, enabling hardware-specific optimizations and seamless adaptation to different computing environments.\n\nThe solution leverages state-of-the-art speech AI models, including Whisper and Qwen3-ASR, and is built upon proven open-source technologies such as Sherpa-ONNX and ONNX Runtime for speech recognition and AI inference. This modular design allows customers to integrate and upgrade AI models with minimal engineering effort.\n\nTo deliver real-time performance and low latency, the platform is optimized for Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Elite-based devices, taking advantage of advanced CPU, GPU, and NPU acceleration capabilities. This enables efficient on-device AI processing while reducing cloud dependency, improving privacy, responsiveness, and operational costs.",
