        "Name of your project": "OpenVoice: A Model for the Language-Blind",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "OpenVoice is an Edge AI-powered real-time speech translation device designed to help workers communicate seamlessly across language barriers. The system performs speech recognition, translation, and speech synthesis entirely on-device, enabling low-latency bilingual conversations even in noisy industrial environments and areas with limited internet connectivity.  The solution targets communication between Vietnamese, English speakers in factories, construction sites, logistics centers, and other multilingual workplaces.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Unlike conventional translation applications that rely heavily on cloud services, OpenVoice operates entirely on-device using Edge AI, ensuring low latency, privacy, and reliability in environments with unstable connectivity.\n\nThe system incorporates industrial terminology memory, context-aware translation, and real-time speech-to-speech interaction optimized for workplace communication. By focusing on workers in industrial environments, the solution addresses a practical communication gap that existing consumer-oriented translation tools often overlook.\n\nAdditionally, the design prioritizes hands-free operation, noise robustness, and deployment on resource-constrained edge devices.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "The system follows a fully on-device Edge AI pipeline:\n\nMicrophone Input\n→ Voice Activity Detection (VAD)\n→ Noise Suppression\n→ Streaming Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR)\n→ Context-Aware Translation Engine\n→ Terminology Memory Retrieval\n→ Streaming Text-to-Speech (TTS)\n→ Speaker Output\n\nThe translation engine is powered by lightweight multilingual language models optimized for NVIDIA Jetson edge devices. Quantization and edge inference techniques are applied to achieve low latency and efficient power consumption.\n\nThe architecture supports real-time processing without cloud dependency while maintaining translation quality in noisy industrial environments.",
