        "Name of your project": "DuoVoice – A Two-Way Edge-AI Translation Ecosystem for Noisy Industrial Environments",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "DuoVoice is an offline, Edge-AI powered real-time translation ecosystem designed for multilingual communication in noisy industrial environments such as factories and construction sites. The system uses a Client–Host architecture consisting of a lightweight bone-conduction headset (DuoVoice Clip-on) connected to a chest-mounted processing unit (DuoVoice Base). It enables hands-free, two-way Vietnamese–Mandarin translation without requiring an Internet connection while allowing workers to remain aware of surrounding safety alarms and environmental sounds.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "DuoVoice differentiates itself by combining real-time offline AI translation with industrial safety-oriented hardware design. Unlike existing consumer translation devices, it features:\n   A magnetic breakaway connector that automatically detaches if the cable becomes entangled, reducing the risk of neck and head injuries.\n   Open-ear bone conduction technology, allowing users to hear alarms, machinery, and nearby coworkers while receiving translated speech.\n   Dual-MEMS differential noise cancellation to improve speech recognition accuracy in environments with 70–85 dBA industrial noise.\n   Voice-activated Selective-Channel Mode, enabling users to communicate privately with selected coworkers in crowded workplaces.\n   A fully on-device AI pipeline, eliminating dependence on cloud services or Internet connectivity and ensuring low latency, privacy, and reliable operation in remote industrial sites.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "DuoVoice adopts an Edge-AI architecture where all processing is performed on a chest-mounted processing unit equipped with an AI SoC, while the headset remains lightweight with only analog components.\nThe AI pipeline consists of:\n   Voice Activity Detection (VAD): SileroVAD or WebRTC VAD to detect speech and reduce unnecessary computation.\n   Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR): Streaming Conformer or Whisper-tiny, optimized with INT8/INT4 quantization for real-time processing.\n   Neural Machine Translation (NMT): Quantized Qwen 2.5-1.5B model for high-quality Vietnamese–Mandarin translation.\n   Text-to-Speech (TTS): VITS-VI and MeloTTS-ZH for natural Vietnamese and Mandarin speech synthesis.\n   Speaker Identification: x-vector or d-vector models supporting the Selective-Channel communication feature.\nThe hardware includes:\n   Bone-conduction headset with dual MEMS microphones.\n   Chest-mounted Edge-AI processing unit with Qualcomm-class NPU, BLE 5.2 LE Audio, ADC/DAC codec, rechargeable battery, and offline language models.\n   Magnetic pogo-pin breakaway connector and analog cable for enhanced industrial safety.\nThe complete translation workflow performs speech recognition, translation, and speech synthesis locally with a target end-to-end latency below 1.5 seconds.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–CN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "DuoVoice aims to improve communication and workplace safety for millions of Vietnamese workers employed in foreign-invested factories and construction sites. By eliminating language barriers, it can reduce misunderstandings during safety instructions, improve collaboration between local workers and foreign supervisors, and increase operational efficiency.\nBecause the system works entirely offline and preserves users' awareness of their surroundings, it is particularly suitable for safety-critical industrial environments where Internet connectivity is limited and continuous situational awareness is essential.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "DuoVoice is designed to evolve into a commercial B2B industrial safety product for factories, construction companies, and PPE equipment providers. The project roadmap includes prototype development, laboratory validation, and field trials in multilingual industrial workplaces.\nFuture development includes:\nExpanding support to additional language pairs such as Vietnamese–English.\nDeploying pilot systems in FDI factories and construction sites.\nOptimizing AI models for improved translation quality and lower latency.\nScaling manufacturing through partnerships with industrial safety equipment suppliers and enterprise customers.\nThe long-term vision is to establish DuoVoice as a stanard wearable communication solution that integrates AI-powered translation with industrial safety requirements for multilingual workplaces.",
