        "Name of your project": "UniVoice AR-Nav",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "Amultilingual voice-controlled virtual assistant integrated with a real-time digital map. The solution assists visitors and international students with indoor navigation, route guidance, and instant academic or event information lookups within university campuses and complex buildings using natural voice commands.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Seamless Voice & Map Integration: Unlike generic translation tools, this solution bridges real-time speech processing with optimized routing algorithms (enhanced Dijkstra) to provide direct, actionable visual and audio guidance.\nClosed-Domain Context Awareness: The AI is fine-tuned to understand location-specific entities (e.g., specialized lab names, academic jargon, faculty names), yielding far higher accuracy within the campus ecosystem than generic LLMs.\nLow-Latency Streaming Architecture: Built on a highly responsive client-server pipeline, the system handles audio as a continuous stream, enabling near-instantaneous Voice-to-Voice responses without forcing the user to wait for long pauses.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "AI Models:\nSpeech-to-Text (STT): Utilizing Whisper or lightweight, Vietnamese-optimized speech models running on an audio streaming pipeline.\nNLU & Translation: Leveraging fine-tuned Small Language Models (SLMs) for Named Entity Recognition (NER) and high-accuracy context translation between target language pairs.\nText-to-Speech (TTS): Integrating fast, natural synthesis architectures (such as FastSpeech2 or VNG's TTS engine) to deliver immediate audio feedback.\nSystem Design & Methodology:\nA robust Client-Server architecture utilizing WebSockets or gRPC to ensure low-latency, bidirectional audio streaming.\nAn Enhanced Entity-Relationship (EER) database model mapped to a graph network for campus layouts. A server-side implementation of Dijkstra's algorithm computes the optimal path in real-time based on the user's localized coordinates.\nThe backend is fully containerized using Docker to ensure seamless scaling, isolated deployment, and efficient hardware utilization (CPU/GPU).",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Education",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Enhancing International Inclusivity: Breaks down language barriers for foreign students, exchange professors, and international visitors, allowing them to navigate and integrate into the campus environment effortlessly.\nImproving Institutional Efficiency: Reduces the workload on front-desk staff and security personnel by automating routine navigational queries and informational lookup services.\nSetting a Benchmark for Smart Campuses: Demonstrates a practical deployment of real-time Voice AI and spatial computing, proving how conversational AI can turn static traditional infrastructure into an interactive, smart ecosystem.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "B2B Enterprise Expansion: The core system architecture can be licensed and adapted into a SaaS model for other complex indoor environments, such as large commercial shopping malls, international hospitals, transit hubs (airports/train stations), and exhibition centers.\nAR/Wearable Integration: Transitioning the visual interface from mobile screens to Augmented Reality (AR) glasses, creating a hands-free navigation experience where directional arrows and translated text are projected directly into the user's field of view.\nVoice-Driven Administrative Automation: Expanding the NLU scope beyond navigation to allow users to execute tasks via voice, such as booking study rooms, scheduling appointments with professors, or reporting facility maintenance issues directly to the system.",
