        "Name of your project": "SafetyVoice Edge",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "SafetyVoice Edge is an offline, on-device AI translation assistant designed for Vietnamese workers and foreign supervisors in manufacturing environments. The system enables real-time Vietnamese–English voice communication without relying on cloud services or stable internet connection. It combines speech recognition, machine translation, text-to-speech, workplace terminology support, and safety-critical phrase handling to help workers communicate clearly in noisy, hands-busy, and low-connectivity settings.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Most translation tools are built for everyday conversations. SafetyVoice Edge is built for workers. In a factory, people do not always need long conversations — they need to understand short and important instructions quickly, such as where to move, which machine to check, what safety equipment to wear, or when to stop. Our solution focuses on these real workplace moments.\n\nThe system combines offline voice translation with workplace vocabulary, confidence checking, and backup safety phrases. If the translation is uncertain, it can ask the speaker to repeat instead of giving a risky answer. This makes it more practical for noisy, hands-busy environments where clear communication matters. This makes the solution more suitable for factories and industrial sites where misunderstanding can affect productivity, worker safety, and operational coordination.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "We will build an offline Vietnamese–English speech translation system using pretrained models adapted for workplace communication.\n\nThe first prototype will use a compact Whisper-based model for speech recognition, NLLB-200 distilled / EnViT5 / mBART for Vietnamese–English translation, and a lightweight TTS model such as MMS-TTS or Piper/VITS for speech output. The pipeline is: microphone input → noise reduction → speech recognition → translation → confidence check → text-to-speech output.\n\nFor data, we will use public Vietnamese speech and translation datasets such as Common Voice, VIVOS, VietSuperSpeech, PhoMT, IWSLT15, and MTet. We will also create a small domain-specific dataset of factory instructions, safety warnings, numbers, machine names, and worker-supervisor conversations. The final system will be optimized with quantization and model conversion for edge-device deployment.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "SafetyVoice Edge helps Vietnamese workers and foreign supervisors communicate more clearly in factories and industrial sites. By running offline on-device, it can support real-time communication even in noisy or low-connectivity environments. The expected impact is fewer misunderstandings, better safety, faster coordination, and more inclusive multilingual workplaces.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "SafetyVoice Edge could become a portable translation device or mobile app for factories, warehouses, and industrial teams. The first version would focus on Vietnamese–English communication, then expand to other languages and company-specific vocabulary. It could be deployed through factories, industrial parks, training centers, or hardware partners.",
