        "Name of your project": "EdgePolyglot",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "The project develops a real-time, fully offline bilingual translation device based on Edge AI technology. The solution integrates a pipeline of Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR), Neural Machine Translation (NMT), and Text-to-Speech (TTS) models running directly on the Qualcomm Snapdragon processor platform, serving workers in noisy environments without internet connectivity.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Unlike cloud-based translation applications that suffer from high latency and frequent disruptions, our solution applies a 'Latency-Aware Pipeline' architecture combined with dynamic chunking to achieve ultra-low First-Packet Latency (FPL). Processing directly on Qualcomm's NPU chip solves data privacy and energy consumption issues. Additionally, we integrate anti-noise algorithms (such as industrial noise cancellation technology) to ensure high accuracy (WER/SyER) even in noisy factory environments.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "Hardware & Optimization: Utilize the Qualcomm Snapdragon platform (e.g., Snapdragon X2 Elite or 8 Elite). Export models to the ONNX standard and execute them via the ONNX Runtime library integrated with the QNN Execution Provider (QNN-EP) to offload computations to the NPU (Hexagon).  \n\nASR Model (Speech Recognition): Apply the Zipformer architecture with linear attention, which is quantized and resolves the NPU's 'Dynamic Shapes' barrier using fixed-padding chunking techniques.  \n\nNMT Model (Machine Translation): Use compact Small Language Models (SLMs) optimized on the NPU, such as Qwen 1.5B/3B (quantized to INT4) via the Qualcomm AI Hub, to process multilingual contexts.  \n\nTTS Model (Speech Synthesis): Deploy ultra-lightweight streaming VITS architectures (like Piper) through the Sherpa-ONNX framework to output audio instantly without waiting for the entire sentence to be translated.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN, VN–CN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Our solution aims to bridge the daily communication gap between foreign technical experts and local workers on FDI manufacturing floors. By providing reliable, offline translation in high-noise environments, we expect to minimize production errors and equipment downtime caused by misunderstandings. Most importantly, it proactively mitigates occupational safety risks. Given that language-related miscommunication is a root cause in approximately 25% of workplace accidents, our hands-free device ensures that critical safety protocols and hazard warnings are accurately understood in real-time.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "To move towards commercialization, the project will build a Sovereign AI data strategy by using license-clean datasets (like BUD500) and avoiding non-commercial licenses (CC-BY-NC-ND). The software solution will be designed to integrate into affordable wearable devices, such as True Wireless earbuds or worker neckbands. We will target a B2B (business-to-business enterprise licensing) business model for FDI factories that need to equip thousands of their workers with secure communication tools without requiring Wi-Fi infrastructure.",
