        "Name of your project": "MoYi - Personalized Edge AI Translation Companion",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "MoYi is a real-time, on-device conversational translation assistant designed for multilingual work environments such as factories, logistics, construction sites, hospitals, and FDI businesses. The solution helps Vietnamese workers communicate with managers, colleagues, or foreign clients through instant voice translation/subtitles. Unlike conventional machine translation, MoYi offers personalization based on job role, personal context, company terminology, and conversation history. After each conversation, the system automatically saves vocabulary, sentence patterns, industry terminology, and safe commands into a personal language learning database, helping users communicate more effectively after each shift.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "The key difference lies in the combination of real-time translation, personal context, company knowledge, learning memory, and safety-first translation.\n\nInstead of simply translating sentences individually, the system understands who the user is, what industry they work in, what terminology they frequently encounter, and what processes or abbreviations their company uses. This results in translations that are more relevant to the real-world context.\n\nFurthermore, the solution transforms each conversation into personalized learning data: vocabulary, work phrases, flashcards, sample responses, and common pronunciation errors. For sentences related to workplace safety, the system can prioritize accurate translation, highlight important sentences, or request confirmation if the audio is unclear. This is a differentiating approach compared to typical translation apps because the product focuses on safe communication in the workplace, personalization for each user, and the ability to deploy Edge AI privately.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "The system is designed using a pipeline:\n→ Voice Activity Detection + Noise Reduction\n→ Streaming ASR + Language Detection\n→ Realtime Translation\n→ Personal Context Retrieval\n→ Safety-first Translation Check\n→ Voice Output / Subtitle / Quick Reply\n→ Learning Memory\n\nMVP uses a real-time ASR model, machine translation, and local context memory. The main components include:\nRealtime Translation: Listening, language recognition, translation, speech reproduction, or subtitle display\nPersonal Context: Personalization based on user, role, industry, and language proficiency\nCompany Knowledge: Storing proprietary terminology, SOPs, commands, safety procedures, and internal abbreviations\nLearning Memory: Storing vocabulary, sentence patterns, flashcards, and work phrases after each shift\nSafety-first Translation: Prioritizing accuracy for safety commands, warnings, or requiring confirmation if the sentence is unclear\n\nIn the initial stage, the system can use local profiles, glossaries, and vector memory to personalize translations without needing fine-tuning the model. The next stage will explore on-device optimization using quantization, small models, local retrieval, lightweight LoRA/adapters, or federated learning to personalize directly on the device while still protecting user data. Qualcomm AI Hub now offers Whisper/ASR models optimized for edge inference, including quantized versions, suitable as a reference for on-device speech recognition deployments.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–CN, VN–KR, VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Prototype",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Other",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "MoYi helps reduce language barriers in international work environments, especially for Vietnamese workers working with foreign managers, colleagues, or clients. The solution can reduce communication misunderstandings, support workplace safety, help users receive work instructions faster, and reduce reliance on interpreters in daily situations.\n\nBeyond the immediate impact on communication, the product also helps users learn foreign languages ​​through their actual work. Each conversation can become vocabulary, sentence patterns, flashcards, and personal knowledge, helping workers improve their communication skills after each shift.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "In the future, MoYi could develop into a wearable translation device or mobile application running Edge AI for workers, technicians, logistics personnel, hospital staff, and service personnel. The product could be deployed in a B2B model for FDI businesses, where each company can configure its own glossary, SOP, safety procedures, and internal phrasebook.\n\nIn the long term, the solution could expand into a Personalized Edge AI Communication Platform for multiple industries, multiple language pairs, and multiple forms of communication: live conversations, team meetings, employee training, customer support, and safety guidance.",
