        "Applicant type": "Team",
        "Participant/Team details: Please fill in the template": "https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1nU3dPiQvuV2CR_uxgIDZZGq1KzMVcUMdiUYNL_ogqa0/edit?usp=sharing",
        "Name of your project": "VoxSync",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "Our solution combines on-device ASR, machine translation, and speech synthesis with hardware-assisted noise cancellation to enable seamless communication between multilingual supervisors and factory workers. The entire AI pipeline runs locally on Android devices, ensuring low latency, complete data privacy, and uninterrupted operation without internet connectivity. Designed specifically for noisy factory settings, OneVoiceAI helps improve workplace communication, operational efficiency, and safety while remaining simple to deploy and use.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "VoxSync is a fully offline, Edge AI-powered simultaneous translation solution designed specifically for industrial workplaces. Unlike conventional cloud-based translators that depend on internet connectivity and introduce network latency, VoxSync processes all speech data locally on NPU-enabled Android devices, guaranteeing privacy, reliability, and uninterrupted operation.\n\nThe platform delivers hands-free, real-time multilingual communication without requiring push-to-talk interactions. By combining professional-grade ENC microphones with a low-latency AI pipeline consisting of VAD, streaming ASR, adaptive machine translation, and on-device TTS, VoxSync remains effective even in factory environments with noise levels above 80 dB.\n\nWith end-to-end translation latency below 1.5 seconds and a simplified Kiosk Mode deployment model, VoxSync enables seamless communication between supervisors and workers while minimizing operational complexity and training requirements.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "Our technical approach leverages a 100% offline, hardware-integrated Edge AI architecture tailored for low latency and high-noise environments:  \n\nHardware Architecture: Powered by enterprise Android devices with dedicated NPUs (Snapdragon, min 8GB RAM). It mandates professional hardware-level Environmental Noise Cancellation (ENC) boom-mics to filter factory noise physically before processing.\n  \nAI Models & Software Pipeline: \n- Voice Activation: Silero VAD acts as a gatekeeper for continuous speech detection.  - Speech Recognition (ASR): Zipformer/Conformer-CTC via Sherpa-ONNX for high-speed streaming.  \n- Machine Translation (MT): Distilled and INT8-quantized models paired with an Adaptive Wait-k policy for real-time translation.  \n- Speech Synthesis (TTS): Lightweight VITS running locally via ONNX.  \n\nSystem Design & Methodology: Built natively on Android (Kotlin/C++ via JNI) to maximize NPU/CPU efficiency and prevent thermal throttling. The entire ecosystem operates as a locked Kiosk application with strict data air-gapping—ensuring 100% offline security with under 1.5-second end-to-end latency.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Our solution will drive significant operational improvements on the factory floor by seamlessly bridging the communication gap between foreign management and local Vietnamese workers",
