        "Name of your project": "Swift Voice",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "Our solution is a fully on-device Speech-to-Speech Translation (S2ST) system for English–Vietnamese communication in noisy manufacturing environments, enabling private, offline, and low-latency interactions between foreign experts and local workers.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Unlike standard S2ST systems that struggle with industrial noise and linguistic latency, our approach introduces three key innovations:\n- Non-Stationary Noise Resilience: We integrate a deep filtering network that eliminates complex mechanical noises (e.g., metal clanking, machinery hiss) without distorting the speaker's voice.  \n- Aggressive Latency Reduction via Streaming MT: We implement a streaming translation model using an adaptive Wait-k policy, allowing the system to translate partial sentences on the fly instead of waiting for full utterances.  \n- Bilingual Code-Switching TTS: Our text-to-speech module naturally handles English-Vietnamese code-switching.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "We employ a deeply quantized, feature-based Cascade pipeline optimized for edge computing:\n- Noise Filter: DeepFilterNet3 operating at 48kHz for multi-frame complex filtering.\n- VAD: Silero VAD v5 with an aggressively shortened dynamic silence threshold to capture rapid speech turns.  \n- ASR: Whisper Large V3 Turbo compiled via CTranslate2 using int8_float16 mixed quantization to significantly reduce memory footprint while maximizing execution speed. \n- Machine Translation (MT): NLLB-200-distilled-1.3B deployed with an adaptive Wait-k decoding strategy.  \n- TTS: VieNeu-TTS-v3-Turbo for low-latency, dual-language audio synthesis.  \n- Hardware: The architecture is fundamentally optimized for resource-constrained edge devices. By leveraging low-bit quantization, ONNX Runtime, and CPU-friendly execution, the system can run efficiently on low-power industrial PCs or embedded devices, utilizing strict compute management to ensure thermal stability.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "This solution will break down language barriers on the manufacturing floor, directly bridging the communication gap between foreign management and local operators. By providing natural, real-time bilingual conversations offline, it will significantly reduce operational errors, improve training efficiency, and accelerate response times to machinery defects without compromising enterprise data privacy.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "In the future, this software pipeline could be embedded into wearable industrial hardware, such as smart earpieces, walkie-talkies, or safety helmet attachments. Additionally, we plan to implement hot-swappable domain-specific glossaries and voice cloning (LoRA adapters) to easily scale and customize the product for various manufacturing sectors",
