        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "●\tCurrent translation machines require manual operation, rely on internet connectivity, and are easily disrupted by environmental noise.\n●\tOur solution overcomes this by being 100% offline, hands-free, and highly noise-resistant.\n●\tInstead of purchasing expensive embedded boards, the project uses a \"Mobile-based Dedicated Edge Device\" strategy to optimize both cost and performance.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "●\tHardware: We utilize a Snapdragon-powered Android smartphone (configured in Kiosk mode) worn in an arm or chest band. It operates using the phone's built-in microphone and speaker, with the flexibility to connect optional external mics or speakers if needed.\n●\tMethodology & Optimization: All AI processing runs locally without the Cloud. We strictly optimize the AI models to run directly on the Snapdragon chip's Hexagon NPU using the Qualcomm AI Hub, which reduces latency to under 1.5 seconds and saves battery.\n●\tSystem Pipeline:\n\tFront-End: Voice Activity Detection (VAD) automatically triggers recording when someone speaks and filters out environmental noise.\n\tSpeech-to-Text: Audio is processed by the Whisper-Tiny model (quantized to INT4) on the NPU to convert speech to text.\n\tTranslation: The text is passed through a Small Language Model (SLM) like Gemma-2B or Phi-3 running on the NPU for translation.\n\tText-to-Speech: The translated text is converted into voice and played through the speaker.",
