        "Name of your project": "OneVoice Lens",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "OneVoice Lens is an audio-only offline AI glasses system for real-time multilingual communication. The glasses act as a lightweight microphone and speaker device, while a Snapdragon phone runs the full AI pipeline locally: speech recognition, machine translation, text-to-speech, and safety-intent detection. The goal is to enable natural bilingual conversation without internet access, especially in noisy, hands-busy work environments.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Most translation devices focus only on casual conversation. OneVoice Lens is designed for real-world operational environments such as factories, construction sites, logistics hubs, and service teams. It adds a danger-first translation mode that detects urgent commands and converts them into short, immediate alerts such as “Stop”, “Forklift behind you”, or “Move back”. The system is offline, wearable, low-friction, and optimized for fast response instead of only sentence-level translation accuracy.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "The system uses an Android Snapdragon phone as the offline AI engine and audio glasses as the wearable interface. Audio is captured from the glasses microphone and streamed to the phone. The phone runs a pipeline of VAD/noise suppression, ASR, machine translation, TTS, and safety-intent classification. Models will be optimized using Qualcomm AI Hub, QNN, and Qualcomm GenAI/Genie where suitable. The prototype will benchmark latency, RTF, ASR/MT/TTS speed, memory usage, and actual backend execution on Qualcomm hardware. The glasses prototype will use Bluetooth audio for microphone input and speaker/bone-conduction output.",
