        "Name of your project": "EdgeStream.AI",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "We propose a real-time multilingual voice translation system optimized for on-device execution on Qualcomm hardware. The solution is built as a streaming ASR → MT → TTS pipeline with Voice Activity Detection feature that continuously processes speech in small chunks, enabling natural, near real-time translation without requiring users to wait for full utterances or perform additional interactions.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "What makes our solution different is that we adapt a standard ASR → MT → TTS pipeline into a true real-time, edge-optimized streaming system, rather than a cloud-based or turn-by-turn setup. \n\nWe design for continuous low-latency inference on Qualcomm devices, and specifically address real-world usage issues through noise robustness (VAD + denoising) and domain adaptation via keyword biasing and lightweight LoRA tuning, ensuring the system remains stable and accurate in noisy, context-specific conversations.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "We propose a modular speech translation system composed of ASR, MT, and TTS components, designed for efficient real-time deployment on mobile and Snapdragon-based edge devices.\n\nFor ASR, we use Zipformer enhanced with domain adaptation techniques such as keyword biasing to improve recognition of context-specific terms. We integrate voice activity detection (VAD) directly into the pipeline using state-of-the-art lightweight models such as SileroVAD or TenVAD to enable accurate real-time speech segmentation and stable streaming inference. We also apply lightweight speech denoising methods to improve robustness in noisy environments. For machine translation (MT), we first benchmark a quantized version of MiLMMT-1B as a strong baseline, and further explore LLM-based and domain-aware translation approaches to improve contextual accuracy across languages. For TTS, we experiment with and benchmark neural speech synthesis models such as PiperTTS, NeuTTS, and ConvNextTTS, including fine-tuning when necessary to balance naturalness and efficiency.\n\nOverall, the system is designed as a fully streaming pipeline optimized for low-latency inference, on-device execution, and robust performance in real-world noisy and domain-specific scenarios.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN, VN–CN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Other",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "We expect our solution to make real-time cross-language communication feel more natural and usable in situations where people currently struggle to interact smoothly—especially when they are moving, working with their hands, or in noisy environments where typing or waiting for turn-based translation is impractical.\n\nBy running directly on edge devices, it reduces the friction of needing internet access or external apps, making translation more immediately available in everyday interactions like quick conversations, on-site coordination, or spontaneous communication between speakers of different languages.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "nan",
