        "Participant/Team details: Please fill in the template": "https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1faxhIDg5xPNcgzK8XhC1BO6Sf09MNcar/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=114921578786512151038&rtpof=true&sd=true",
        "Name of your project": "Multimodal EdgeVoice Collar - Vision-Enhanced Offline Translator for Industrial Workplaces",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "A multimodal wearable translation neckband that combines Edge AI, NLP, and Computer Vision. It features a micro-camera for real-time visual-assisted audio beamforming (noise cancellation) and instant on-device OCR translation of machine screens/safety signs, delivered via bone-conduction audio to keep workers' ears open and safe.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Unlike generic audio translators, our solution is multimodal. It solves the critical industrial noise problem by using CV-guided face tracking to focus the physical/digital microphone beam directly on the speaker's mouth. Additionally, it features offline OCR to translate warning labels and machinery control panels (Chinese/Korean/English ↔ Vietnamese) instantly, providing hands-free operation and maximum situational awareness.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "1. Hardware: Powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon SoC using its dedicated NPU to run concurrent models.\n2. CV Pipeline: On-device lightweight Face Detection (e.g., BlazeFace optimized via Qualcomm AI Hub) to guide directional audio beamforming. A quantized MobileNet-OCR model for instant text extraction from images.\n3. Audio & NLP Pipeline: Speech-to-Text via INT8 quantized Whisper-Tiny, translation using a compact Neural Machine Translation (NMT) model, and Text-to-Speech via FastSpeech2.\n4. Performance target: Total turnaround latency < 1.5s, Real-Time Factor < 1.0, operating 100% offline.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN, VN–CN, VN–KR",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Manufacturing",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "1. Safety & Health: By utilizing bone-conduction audio instead of traditional ear-blocking headphones, workers maintain full situational awareness on busy factory floors, eliminating safety hazards and accident risks.\n2. Productivity & Skills Transfer: It bridges the communication gap between foreign experts (e.g. from China, Korea) and Vietnamese workers. This accelerates machine-operating training, reduces assembly errors, and increases factory throughput.\n3. Data Security & Independence: Running 100% offline (on-device) ensures complete confidentiality of factory processes and blueprints, making it compliant with strict industrial security regulations where cloud-connected devices are banned.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "- Phase 1 (MVP Validation): Optimize the AI models (Whisper-Tiny, MobileNet-OCR) via Qualcomm AI Hub and test them on Snapdragon developer boards with a 3D-printed prototype. \n- Phase 2 (Industrial Pilot): Design a rugged, IP67 dust-and-waterproof neckband casing. Partner with local manufacturing plants (FDI companies in HCMC/Binh Duong) for a 1-month pilot run to gather user feedback. \n- Phase 3 (B2B Commercialization): Sell the hardware directly to industrial companies as smart personal protective equipment (PPE). Offer customized local dictionaries (domain-specific terms for electronics, textiles, or automotive manufacturing) as a subscription service.",
