        "Participant/Team details: Please fill in the template": "https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1RacQ07Y3VES1DZEoitYSmRTk42b5YfLodLA91Pj3fkk/edit?usp=sharing",
        "Name of your project": "Flying Translator & First Responder",
        "Briefly describe your proposed solution": "Our solution is an Edge AI-Powered Multilingual Smart GCS (Ground Control Station) & Field Intercom designed for industrial autonomous operations (logistics hubs, mega construction sites, and offshore facilities). It integrates a completely offline, real-time voice translation pipeline directly into portable ground control hardware and field communication relays.The system enables international engineers, drone pilots, and hands-busy ground crews to communicate seamlessly across language barriers (Vietnamese $\\leftrightarrow$ English/Mandarin/Korean) via localized audio synthesis and heads-up text overlays. By processing everything locally on Qualcomm edge processors, the solution ensures continuous, sub-2-second latency translation even in remote environments with zero cellular or internet connectivity, allowing operators to execute mission-critical voice commands and field coordination flawlessly.",
        "What makes your solution innovative or different from exi...": "Unlike generic translation apps or standard cloud-based APIs (which fail entirely in remote industrial zones due to poor connectivity), our solution introduces three distinct innovations:\n\nContextual Form-Factor Integration: Instead of a standalone smartphone app, the translation pipeline is natively embedded into the tactical field communication infrastructure and GCS software. It directly bridges telemetry monitoring with voice communication, tailored for high-risk, \"hands-busy\" workflows.\n\nAcoustic Resilience for Extreme Environments: Standard translation models degrade rapidly under heavy industrial noise or drone propeller hums. Our solution features a specialized, lightweight neural speech enhancement layer that filters extreme ambient noise before routing audio to the ASR pipeline, preserving high translation accuracy (BLEU/COMET scores).\n\nAd-Hoc Network Relay Capability: The system utilizes decentralized peer-to-peer data linking. If one field agent is completely out of range, the voice packets and translated tokens are intelligently routed and steered across local hardware nodes, maintaining unbreakable voice coordination across distributed teams without relying on infrastructure.",
        "Describe your technical approach": "Our technical architecture is meticulously optimized for local execution on Qualcomm hardware to guarantee a Real-Time Factor (RTF) $< 1.0$ and a turnaround latency under $2.0$ seconds:Hardware Layer: Powered by Qualcomm Snapdragon/Flight platforms or Qualcomm IoT processors, maximizing the compute efficiency of the on-device Hexagon NPU and DSP to offload heavy neural network operations from the CPU.On-Device AI Pipeline (Quantized & Optimized):Front-end: A hardware-accelerated RNNoise/DeepFilterNet layer for real-time industrial noise suppression.ASR (Speech-to-Text): A quantized INT8 Whisper-small variant, optimized via the Qualcomm Neural Processing SDK to achieve high character recognition accuracy locally.MT (Machine Translation): A highly compressed, specialized distillation of MarianMT / NLLB models fine-tuned for industrial, technical, and operational terminology.TTS (Text-to-Speech): A lightweight VITS model optimized for fast, natural-sounding multi-speaker prosody generation to ensure a high Mean Opinion Score (MOS).Software & System Design: The core translation pipeline is engineered in C++ for bare-metal execution speed and ultra-low memory footprint. This backend is wrapped with native bindings into a cross-platform Flutter-based Ground Control application, rendering real-time translated text logs alongside live telemetry data while simultaneously triggering the local audio synthesis.",
        "Expected language pair to support": "VN–EN",
        "Project's current development phase": "Idea",
        "Real-world use case or industry your solution be applied": "Construction",
        "What impact do you expect your solution to create?": "Our solution introduces a paradigm shift in how field teams operate in high-risk, multi-national environments by delivering impact across three critical vectors:\n\nUncompromising Operational Safety: In heavy industries like autonomous drone deployments, maritime logistics, or mega-construction, a 5-second communication delay or a mistranslated safety command can lead to catastrophic accidents. By delivering sub-2-second, highly accurate offline translations, our system eliminates human error during mission-critical handovers between global supervisors and local ground crews.\n\nTrue Infrastructure Independence: By stripping away reliance on cellular networks and cloud APIs, we ensure 100% operational continuity. Teams working in remote industrial dead zones, offshore platforms, or subterranean environments maintain uninterrupted voice coordination, saving companies thousands of dollars in potential downtime caused by network drops.\n\nDemocratization of Tech & Field Inclusivity: Language barriers often isolate local workforce majorities from specialized foreign technical experts. This solution empowers native-speaking workers with real-time, hands-free audio understanding, directly boosting field efficiency, lowering onboarding friction, and ensuring an inclusive, safer workplace.",
        "How could your solution evolve into a real product or dep...": "We envision a clear, three-tiered commercialization and deployment roadmap that transitions this prototype into a sustainable B2B enterprise ecosystem:\n\nPhase 1: Software Core & GCS SDK (Months 1–6)\nThe optimized C++ pipeline will be packaged into a lightweight, modular SDK. This allows us to license the software as a plug-in for existing enterprise field applications and industrial Ground Control Station (GCS) platforms. Drone fleet operators and logistics firms can instantly unlock on-device translation within their current software suites via simple API integration.\n\nPhase 2: Qualcomm-Powered Turnkey Field Hardware (Months 6–12)\nWe aim to collaborate with hardware manufacturers to embed our Edge AI pipeline directly into dedicated physical devices—such as ruggedized smart walkie-talkies, wearable headsets, or tactical field comm boxes. By utilizing Qualcomm’s energy-efficient IoT platforms, we can deliver a standalone \"Smart Intercom\" product tailored for heavy industrial use cases where smartphones are impractical.\n\nPhase 3: Enterprise B2B SaaS & On-Premise Scaling (Month 12+)\nOur monetization strategy will shift to a B2B licensing model (per-device or enterprise-wide subscription). Future iterations will introduce localized model-adaptation tools, allowing enterprise clients (e.g., global mining conglomerates or civil engineering firms) to securely upload and train the offline models on their proprietary, highly specialized technical jargon on-premise without compromising sensitive data.",
